The brother of MP Simon Danczuk’s wife Karen was re-arrested yesterday after two more women accused him of sexually abusing them.

Police confirmed that Michael Burke, 36, was being questioned last night on suspicion of historic sexual offences a month after complaints from Mrs Danczuk led to his first arrest.

The divorced father of three, a security guard, was held and taken to a Manchester police station yesterday morning after ‘new information came to light’.

